## Amplitude Analytics API Suite

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of APIs for event ingestion, data export, user management, and analytics operations. The platform serves as a product analytics solution with robust data collection, processing, and analysis capabilities designed for enterprise-scale applications.

## Product Relationships and Architecture

The Amplitude API ecosystem consists of several interconnected components organized around core data flows:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- **HTTP V2 API** serves as the primary event ingestion endpoint (`api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi`) for real-time event streaming
- **Batch Event Upload API** handles bulk data ingestion with 20MB payload limits for high-volume scenarios
- **Attribution API** processes mobile advertising attribution data using advertising identifiers (IDFA, ADID, Android App Set ID)

**User and Group Management:**
- **Identify API** manages user property updates and device-to-user ID mappings without generating events
- **Group Identify API** handles group-level properties through the Accounts add-on
- **User Mapping API** provides cross-project user aliasing via the Portfolio add-on

**Data Access and Export:**
- **Export API** enables bulk event data extraction in zipped JSON format
- **Dashboard REST API** provides programmatic access to analytics results including funnels, retention, and segmentation
- **User Profile API** retrieves comprehensive user profiles including computed properties and recommendations

**Compliance and Privacy:**
- **User Privacy API** handles GDPR/CCPA data deletion requests
- **CCPA DSAR API** provides asynchronous data subject access request processing

**Configuration and Metadata:**
- **Taxonomy API** manages event schema, properties, and tracking plans for Enterprise users
- **Lookup Table APIs** (v1 deprecated, v2 current) enable CSV-based property enrichment
- **Behavioral Cohorts API** supports cohort management and synchronization

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `user_id`: Business-defined user identifier
- `device_id`: Device-specific identifier for anonymous tracking
- `amplitude_id`: Internal Amplitude user identifier
- `insert_id`: Deduplication identifier for events
- `session_id`: Session tracking identifier

**Event Structure:**
- `event_type`: Categorical event name
- `event_properties`: Event-specific metadata
- `user_properties`: User-level attributes
- `group_properties`: Group-level attributes (Accounts add-on)
- `server_upload_time`: Server-side timestamp in UTC ISO-8601

**Property Operations:**
- `$set`: Set property value
- `$setOnce`: Set only if not previously set
- `$add`: Increment numeric values
- `$append`/`$prepend`: Array operations
- `$unset`: Remove property
- `$remove`: Remove from array

**API Authentication:**
- `api_key`: Project-level authentication for ingestion
- HTTP Basic Authentication: Username/password for data access APIs
- Secret keys: Server-side authentication for profile APIs
- SCIM keys: Identity provider integration authentication

## Product Ecosystem Integration

Amplitude operates as a central analytics hub with multiple integration points:

**Data Sources:** Server-to-server ingestion, mobile SDKs, web SDKs, and third-party integrations via partner_id parameters

**Data Destinations:** Event streaming to external systems with delivery metrics monitoring, cohort synchronization to marketing platforms, and warehouse exports

**Identity Management:** SCIM 2.0 integration with identity providers (Okta, JumpCloud), cross-project user mapping via Portfolio add-on, and attribution matching with 72-hour windows

**Compliance Framework:** Automated data deletion workflows, data subject access request processing, and regional data residency (EU endpoints available)

## API Endpoints and Technical Specifications

**Primary Ingestion Endpoints:**
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi` - HTTP V2 event ingestion
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/batch` - Batch event upload
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/attribution` - Attribution events
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/identify` - User property updates
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/groupidentify` - Group property updates

**Data Access Endpoints:**
- `GET api/2/export` - Event data export
- `GET profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile` - User profile retrieval
- `GET api/3/cohorts` - Cohort management
- `GET data-api.amplitude.com/api/3/lookup_table` - Lookup table operations

**Management Endpoints:**
- `POST api/2/release` - Release annotations
- `POST api/2/annotations` - Chart annotations
- `POST api/2/deletions/users` - User data deletion
- `GET core.amplitude.com/scim/1/` - SCIM user provisioning

**Rate Limits and Constraints:**
- Event ingestion: 1000 events/second per device/user, 500K events/day
- User properties: 1800 updates/hour per user
- Cohort downloads: 500 requests/month (Growth/Enterprise)
- Profile API: 600 requests/minute
- Payload limits: 20MB (batch), 1MB (HTTP V2), 100MB (lookup tables)

The platform supports both real-time and EU data residency requirements with region-specific endpoints, comprehensive error handling with HTTP status codes (400, 413, 429, 503), and extensive monitoring capabilities through delivery metrics and streaming analytics.